<div id="review_204421684" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/204421684" />
    <a title="Kirsten " class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/833700-kirsten"><img alt="Kirsten " src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1607003371p2/833700.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/204421684?book_show_action=true">Mar 19, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Kirsten " class="user" itemprop="url" name="Kirsten " href="/user/show/833700-kirsten">Kirsten </a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780140063554" href="/book/show/2215118.Black_Lamb_and_Grey_Falcon">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer204421684" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12620739525492039548">Years ago, I read a book by <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/6970.Robert_D__Kaplan' title='Robert D. Kaplan' rel='nofollow noopener'>Robert D. Kaplan</a> called <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/33690.Balkan_Ghosts_A_Journey_Through_History' title='Balkan Ghosts A Journey Through History by Robert D. Kaplan' rel='nofollow noopener'>Balkan Ghosts: A Journey Through History</a>. It inspired me to attempt to read this doorstop of a book. It took me quite a while but I finally got through it. <br/><br/>My copy had a horrible typeface so that is probably why it took me so long. <br/><br/>Don&apos;t let that put you off. Don&apos;t let the 1100+ pages put you off. This book is absorbing, interesting, and compelling. You see the incredible diversity of the Balkan region, you see just what an injustice the Europe</span>
  <span id="freeText12620739525492039548" style="display:none">Years ago, I read a book by <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/6970.Robert_D__Kaplan" title="Robert D. Kaplan" rel="nofollow noopener">Robert D. Kaplan</a> called <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/33690.Balkan_Ghosts_A_Journey_Through_History" title="Balkan Ghosts A Journey Through History by Robert D. Kaplan" rel="nofollow noopener">Balkan Ghosts: A Journey Through History</a>. It inspired me to attempt to read this doorstop of a book. It took me quite a while but I finally got through it. <br /><br />My copy had a horrible typeface so that is probably why it took me so long. <br /><br />Don't let that put you off. Don't let the 1100+ pages put you off. This book is absorbing, interesting, and compelling. You see the incredible diversity of the Balkan region, you see just what an injustice the European powers did to the Balkans with the Treaty of Versailles after WW I. You can even see the storm clouds gathering and spreading out from Germany. <br /><br />I loved this and would love to read more histories of some of these states. </span>
  <a data-text-id="12620739525492039548" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


